    "text_7": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Quick Q&A with Jack from Walker Golf",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Q: What makes Walker Golf different from other brands out there?</strong><br/><br/><strong>Jack:</strong> \"We have deep roots in both skate and golf, and that balance shows up in everything we do. Plus, we just really care about this. We've been playing our whole lives.\"</p><p><strong>Q: How would you describe your target customer?</strong><br/><br/><strong>Jack:</strong> \"Honestly? We don't really have one. We're just making what we love and hoping others are stoked on it too. That said, if we had to pick, it's probably a mid-30s Aussie dad who plays twice a week.\"</p><p><strong>Q: Any musical influences in the brand?</strong><br/><br/><strong>Jack:</strong> \"Yeah we've got friends in bands like Tame Impala and Skegss. A lot of our shoots and trips are just hanging out with our mates and making cool stuff together.\"</p><p><strong>Q: Favorite place to play golf?</strong><br/><br/><strong>Jack:</strong> \"The west side of Oahu. It's kind of a dream. Surf in the morning, golf in the afternoon.\"</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": ["heading_1", "text_1"],
      "settings": {
        "alignment": "left",
        "enable_animation": true
      }
    },
